text: Excellent kaya toast set for a very reasonable price (S$3.80 for butter kaya set). Fast and friendly service.

There's something sweet and granular in the kaya toast like sprinkled sugar which doesn't suit my taste. The butter is also not salty enough. Eggs are done well though. And stall looks clean. Is it really open 24hours?

Great service by the boss.. asked me to sit while he prepped my order and brought the kaya toast, eggs and coffee to me when ready. (Didn't expect this, but it wasn't too busy at the time)
Updated opening hours 0630- approx. 1400 daily, and closed on Tuesdays
Toast bread is crispy n soft. Service is excellent. Served to you when not crowded
